    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. it looks good. can you give me one more version that's maybe a little less \"standard\"? i want it to feel slightly more personal and less like a template, just something that shows we actually appreciated their personality during the interview process. nothing too casual, just... warmer?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a smart move; a warmer tone can make a huge difference in maintaining good relationships. You want to move beyond the standard corporate script and sound like a real person who enjoyed the conversation.\n\nHere is a slightly warmer version that still maintains high professionalism. It focuses more on the *experience* of interviewing them, rather than just the outcome.\n\nSubject: Following up on the Senior DevOps opportunity at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out regarding the Senior DevOps role. The entire team thoroughly enjoyed getting to know you throughout this process. Your insights into Kubernetes and your approach to AWS were genuinely fascinating, and it was clear you bring a thoughtful, high-level perspective to your work. While we ultimately decided to move forward with another candidate whose background aligned perfectly with a very specific, immediate project need, please know that this was an incredibly tough decision.\n\nWe truly appreciated the energy and personality you brought to our conversations. We hope you'll keep us in mind as your career progresses, and we wish you nothing but success in finding the perfect next challenge.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n\n***\n\n*This version uses words like \"thoroughly enjoyed\" and \"gen",
      "source": "target",
